{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"Sensor","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor_APIs\">Sensor APIs</a></strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor\"><code>Sensor</code></a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Properties</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor/activated\"><code>activated</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor/hasReading\"><code>hasReading</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor/timestamp\"><code>timestamp</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Methods</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor/start\"><code>start()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor/stop\"><code>stop()</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Events</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor/activate_event\"><code>activate</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor/error_event\"><code>error</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor/reading_event\"><code>reading</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Inheritance:</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/EventTarget\"><code>EventTarget</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Related pages for Sensor API</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/AbsoluteOrientationSensor\"><code>AbsoluteOrientationSensor</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Accelerometer\"><code>Accelerometer</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/AmbientLightSensor\"><code>AmbientLightSensor</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/GravitySensor\"><code>GravitySensor</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Gyroscope\"><code>Gyroscope</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/LinearAccelerationSensor\"><code>LinearAccelerationSensor</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Magnetometer\"><code>Magnetometer</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/OrientationSensor\"><code>OrientationSensor</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/RelativeOrientationSensor\"><code>RelativeOrientationSensor</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/SensorErrorEvent\"><code>SensorErrorEvent</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>The <strong><code>Sensor</code></strong> interface of the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor_APIs\">Sensor APIs</a> is the base class for all the other sensor interfaces. This interface cannot be used directly. Instead it provides properties, event handlers, and methods accessed by interfaces that inherit from it.</p>\n<p>If a feature policy blocks use of a feature it is because your code is inconsistent with the policies set on your server. This is not something that would ever be shown to a user. The <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/Feature-Policy\"><code>Feature-Policy</code></a> HTTP header article contains implementation instructions.</p><svg viewBox=\"-1 -1 650 42\" preserveAspectRatio=\"xMinYMin meet\">\n  <a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" xlink:href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/EventTarget\">\n    <rect x=\"0\" y=\"0\" width=\"88\" height=\"25\" fill=\"#fff\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" stroke-width=\"2px\"></rect>\n    <text x=\"44\" y=\"16\" font-size=\"10px\" fill=\"#4D4E53\" text-anchor=\"middle\">\n      EventTarget\n    </text>\n  </a>\n  <line x1=\"88\" y1=\"14\" x2=\"118\" y2=\"14\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" \"=\"\"></line>\n  <polyline points=\"88,14 98,9 98,19 88,14\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" fill=\"#fff\"></polyline>\n  <a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" xlink:href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor\" aria-current=\"page\">\n    <rect x=\"118\" y=\"0\" width=\"75\" height=\"25\" fill=\"#F4F7F8\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" stroke-width=\"2px\"></rect>\n    <text x=\"155.5\" y=\"16\" font-size=\"10px\" fill=\"#4D4E53\" text-anchor=\"middle\">\n      Sensor\n    </text>\n  </a></svg>\n<p>When initially created, the <code>Sensor</code> object is <em>idle</em>, meaning it does not take measures. Once the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor/start\" title=\"start()\"><code>start()</code></a> method is called, it prepares itself to read data and, once ready, the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor/activate_event\" title=\"activate\"><code>activate</code></a> event is sent and the sensor becomes <em>activated</em>. It then sends a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor/reading_event\" title=\"reading\"><code>reading</code></a> event each time new data is available.</p>\n<p>In case of an error, the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor/error_event\" title=\"error\"><code>error</code></a> event is sent, reading stops, and the <code>Sensor</code> object becomes <em>idle</em> again. The <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor/start\" title=\"start()\"><code>start()</code></a> method needs to be called again before it can read further data.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"interfaces_based_on_sensor","title":"Interfaces based on <code>Sensor</code>","isH3":false,"content":"<p>Below is a list of interfaces based on the <code>Sensor</code> interface.</p>\n<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Accelerometer\"><code>Accelerometer</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/AmbientLightSensor\"><code>AmbientLightSensor</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/GravitySensor\"><code>GravitySensor</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Gyroscope\"><code>Gyroscope</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/LinearAccelerationSensor\"><code>LinearAccelerationSensor</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Magnetometer\"><code>Magnetometer</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/OrientationSensor\"><code>OrientationSensor</code></a></li>\n</ul>","titleAsText":"Interfaces based on Sensor"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"properties","title":"Properties","isH3":false,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"sensor.activated\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor/activated\"><code>Sensor.activated</code></a> <span title=\"This value may not be changed.\" class=\"badge inline readonly\">Read only </span></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Returns a boolean value indicating whether the sensor is active.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"sensor.hasreading\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor/hasReading\"><code>Sensor.hasReading</code></a> <span title=\"This value may not be changed.\" class=\"badge inline readonly\">Read only </span></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Returns a boolean value indicating whether the sensor has a reading.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"sensor.timestamp\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor/timestamp\"><code>Sensor.timestamp</code></a> <span title=\"This value may not be changed.\" class=\"badge inline readonly\">Read only </span></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Returns the time stamp of the latest sensor reading.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"methods","title":"Methods","isH3":false,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"sensor.start\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor/start\"><code>Sensor.start()</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Activates one of the sensors based on <code>Sensor</code>.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"sensor.stop\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor/stop\"><code>Sensor.stop()</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Deactivates one of the sensors based on <code>Sensor</code>.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"events","title":"Events","isH3":false,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"activate\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor/activate_event\" title=\"activate\"><code>activate</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Fired when a sensor becomes activated.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"error\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor/error_event\" title=\"error\"><code>error</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Fired when an exception occurs on a sensor.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"reading\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor/reading_event\" title=\"reading\"><code>reading</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Fired when a new reading is available on a sensor.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://w3c.github.io/sensors/#the-sensor-interface","title":"Generic Sensor API"}],"query":"api.Sensor"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.Sensor","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor/bcd.json"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Interfaces based on <code>Sensor</code>","id":"interfaces_based_on_sensor"},{"text":"Properties","id":"properties"},{"text":"Methods","id":"methods"},{"text":"Events","id":"events"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"}],"summary":"The Sensor interface of the Sensor APIs is the base class for all the other sensor interfaces. This interface cannot be used directly. Instead it provides properties, event handlers, and methods accessed by interfaces that inherit from it.","popularity":0.0004,"modified":"2022-09-09T05:18:40.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"Sensor","locale":"pt-BR","native":"Português (do Brasil)"}],"source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/sensor","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/api/sensor/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/e0e09b1df51489867f2e74c18586d168ba5e00d1","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor","title":"Sensor"}],"pageTitle":"Sensor - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}